{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a ceramic or glass bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh sago and milk into it. Place bowl in refrigerator and leave sago to soak for a minimum 8 hours or overnight.","Grease and line a pudding basin with lid (13 cm) and set aside.","Place lemon zest and dark brown sugar into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>10 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add breadcrumbs, bicarbonate of soda and 40 g unsalted butter and combine <nobr>5 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place pitted dates, dried figs, dried apricots and dried apple into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5-8 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>, or until an evenly chopped consistency is achieved.","Add dried currants, glacé cherries, sultanas, ground allspice, ground cinnamon, ground nutmeg, egg, reserved sago and milk and reserved brown sugar-breadcrumb mixture and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Transfer into prepared pudding basin, cover with a sheet of baking paper and secure lid. Place pudding basin into Varoma dish. Rinse and dry mixing bowl.","Place water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma into position and steam <nobr>60 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Check water level in mixing bowl and top up if necessary. Place Varoma back into position and steam for a further <nobr>60 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Check water level in mixing bowl again and top up if necessary. Place Varoma back into position and steam for a further <nobr>60 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Check water level in mixing bowl again and top up if necessary. Place Varoma back into position and steam for a final <nobr>60 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr> or until pudding is cooked through and consistent in colour. Your pudding is cooked through when a wooden skewer inserted into the centre of the pudding comes out clean. Serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["80 g sago","520 g full cream milk, for soaking","40 g unsalted butter, softened, plus extra for greasing","1 lemon, zest only, no white pith","180 g dark brown sugar","70 g breadcrumbs","1 tsp bicarbonate of soda","60 g pitted dates","60 g dried figs","30 g dried apricots","30 g dried apples","30 g dried currants","30 g glacé cherries","50 g sultanas","1 pinch ground allspice","1 pinch ground cinnamon","1 pinch ground nutmeg","1 egg","1700 g water"]}],"id":"r89851","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-XdNGcvs37UY\/XZannW_-BzI\/AAAAAAAAhBs\/rvVILN2oTKgjSL5-Tlpz-lHs52A3xwuVwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_O4-ihTgIBwIJ6sBi.png","title":"Sago plum pudding","publishedAt":"2015-12-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5.3 g","fat":"7.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"55.6 g","calories":"1300 kJ \/ 309 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ceramic or glass bowl, baking paper, pudding basin with lid (13 cm), wooden skewer, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Serve pudding warm with <em>Brandy cream sauce<\/em> or <em>Brandy cashew cream, <\/em>garnished with fresh cherries.<em><br><\/em>","If using a different size pudding basin or baking tin please be aware cooking times will be lengthened or shortened accordingly. Continue checking water level and topping up as necessary."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","14h 45m","8 portions"]}